📅 Date: 2026-07-04
<br/>📍 Topic / Module Covered: Setup JDK, cLoning Barako repo, UML Diagram

### What I Did Today
 I was able to clone the Barako repository from GitHub using git clone. I tried creating a UML diagram to visualize the classes and relationships in the project.

### What I Learned
 I understood the process of Git cloning and how it helps in obtaining a copy of the project.I realized the importance of UML diagrams in designing object‑oriented programs even before writing any code.
### Problems I Faced
 I encountered an error in Git while fetching/pulling from the remote repository, so I had to check the remote URL and credentials. I was somewhat confused about the correct symbols in the UML diagram (e.g., inheritance vs. association).

### Reflections
Proper setup of the development environment is important to avoid delays in coding.The UML diagram is like a blueprint — the flow of the program becomes clearer when there is a visual representation. Errors in Git are normal, but I am learning how to debug and fix configuration issues.

### Next Steps

- Improve the UML diagram to make the representation of the project classes more complete.

- Practice basic Java programs using the JDK setup.

- Try Git operations (push/pull) again to become more familiar with the workflow.

- Read more about different UML relationships agregation,composition.
